w id="UUID6c08085a-5b70-481a-5097-161dab562894"><entry id="UUIDd2c7def2-6e7f-4d19-4040-986c14fd1071">National Income</entry><entry id="UUID4aa30413-cc3b-4c61-51e8-da05269b9f3a">After-tax Income</entry><entry id="UUID8f62d6e9-4fe6-4781-6898-de63b2e22237">Consumption</entry><entry id="UUIDede3f70b-70bb-4d82-6b73-1d355d96b282">I + G + X</entry><entry id="UUID59ed32ac-9125-4a0b-7a8c-32dd5c8b11af">Minus Imports</entry><entry id="UUIDa374c384-43f0-407d-6636-bd45b4e8e1ac">Aggregate Expenditures</entry></row></thead><tbody id="UUID8ab74bdb-c658-468b-52ec-159e67b49910"><row id="UUIDd95421bd-92dc-439a-4b0d-edb0e267e8f5"><entry id="UUIDeb249562-97bb-4d7a-6321-d5ed8ae034c1">$8,000</entry><entry id="UUIDb7f42d0f-4e9c-4bb4-53ae-f39a861e064c">$4,800</entry><entry id="UUIDbc683d5d-bc25-4e53-632b-3b2e159d089d">$4,340</entry><entry id="UUID57dd1ab6-664c-4e20-7429-9e302d9b2dd1">$5,000</entry><entry id="UUID134893b5-799e-41a9-7f33-4b29ee7f7912">$240</entry><entry id="UUID4bd7c56b-07c8-4381-64a0-79c1ca56466a">$9,100</entry></row><row id="UUID5ade98b3-c423-45cf-59d4-029d6312cc8f"><entry id="UUID7f51a37f-c4dd-4a1a-464a-c9047e01f5f8">$9,000</entry><entry id="UUID3db7e99f-f167-40ef-7901-cc9e2843952c">$5,400</entry><entry id="UUIDa3c5d483-1d99-47af-6287-a34de5d90bb4">$4,820</entry><entry id="UUIDed0324a8-9e2e-4ebf-7b37-89cb3b69774a">$5,000</entry><entry id="UUID1c445a94-4ec8-442b-43f7-9691a6f5a40a">$270</entry><entry id="UUID335f6c44-d57f-44be-5f5e-ea9b1ac0139e">$9,550</entry></row><row id="UUID3ef8baae-5d7a-46be-5804-0bef042c6b23"><entry id="UUID09b7924f-8baf-4e98-735d-5378383d8b25"><emphasis effect="italics">$10,000</emphasis></entry><entry id="UUID059b5511-cedb-4d76-7ef6-84a776851390"><emphasis effect="italics">$6,000</emphasis></entry><entry id="UUIDece15da1-f6a8-4eda-64e5-237eba6555a7"><emphasis effect="italics">$5,300</emphasis></entry><entry id="UUID7e5218f7-8310-4673-49e0-35cca0363089"><emphasis effect="italics">$5,000</emphasis></entry><entry id="UUIDf7d5f392-2121-464c-4d94-09d30c10448d"><emphasis effect="italics">$300</emphasis></entry><entry id="UUIDd45fdb9f-7dd0-406b-6b71-0e6d34b4b32d"><emphasis effect="italics">$10,000</emphasis></entry></row><row id="UUID8571814a-abef-4fb8-43c4-484a42b47139"><entry id="UUIDdba0d9bc-2088-4d30-675e-ed6c579e1dac">$11,000</entry><entry id="UUID958c2b74-547a-4a13-583e-30836fdb8208">$6,600</entry><entry id="UUID07208992-08ce-4b11-7e10-a14c370a47e1">$5,780</entry><entry id="UUID4bbe635f-f130-4b41-47c1-a018e345420e">$5,000</entry><entry id="UUIDe89ab690-f496-475a-42e3-e0fc3708e09a">$330</entry><entry id="UUIDda1de6a4-223d-428a-7826-f01bce59a84b">$10,450</entry></row><row id="UUID82e1cc06-622a-4041-466e-b56d5449d2eb"><entry id="UUID060cf928-143a-41ef-4dd3-af7459577885">$12,000</entry><entry id="UUID25928945-aa85-4dfd-77af-3a89b9221792">$7,200</entry><entry id="UUID97940a19-973a-4dbb-4862-9fa4351d5196">$6,260</entry><entry id="UUIDe2585465-67d8-4221-538c-0db06a3965a7">$5,000</entry><entry id="UUIDb0234ffb-85d6-4cf5-4364-0de111f26d2a">$360</entry><entry id="UUID9bcd21dc-cbd4-4c54-78ec-0e17d5cda32d">$10,900</entry></row><row id="UUIDcd94bf5a-dddd-43f9-5fc4-e6cdd0c1764c"><entry id="UUIDe987dbc5-418d-4211-6ba2-33f21e28c1e7">$13,000</entry><entry id="UUIDa0345720-c61c-4b2f-7cfd-6814775a68d9">$7,800</entry><entry id="UUID4448b7b1-4b20-4073-67d8-ac2e1bfeeab6">$6,240</entry><entry id="UUID506cd783-5fdd-4b18-6ed6-c973550aa8e7">$5,000</entry><entry id="UUID39aeb29b-b6fd-405a-4ea6-db6a4646fadf">$4,390</entry><entry id="UUIDfb5724db-4ee8-48ef-65f9-6c6af49ad867">$11,350</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table>
          <para id="fs-idp17850128">The alternative way of determining equilibrium is to solve for Y, where Y = national income, using: Y = AE = C + I + G + X – M</para>
          <equation id="fs-idp8303616" class="unnumbered"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mtext>Y = $500 + 0.8(Y – T) + $2,000 + $1,000 + $2,000 – 0.05(Y – T)</mtext></math></equation>
          <para id="fs-idp120074224">Solving for Y, we see that the equilibrium level of output is Y = $10,000.</para>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
      <exercise id="fs-idm51414432">
        <problem id="fs-idp36269408">
          <para id="fs-idm58740736">Explain how the multiplier works. Use an MPC of 80% in an example.</para>
        </problem>
        <solution id="eip-idm368923616">
          <para id="fs-idm48927152">The multiplier refers to how many times a dollar will turnover in the economy. It is based on the Marginal Propensity to Consume (MPC) which tells how much of every dollar received will be spent. If the MPC is 80% then this means that out of every one dollar received by a consumer, $0.80 will be spent. This $0.80 is received by another person. In turn, 80% of the $0.80 received, or $0.64, will be spent, and so on. The impact of the multiplier is diluted when the effect of taxes and expenditure on imports is considered. To derive the multiplier, take the 1/1 – F; where F is equal to percent of savings, taxes, and expenditures on imports.</para>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
